No!  I am saying that everyone has the right to be heard, but no one
has the right to keep other people from being heard.  If Usenet were
'made public', it would be subject to government control, and people
with politically-incorrect opinions would be banned.  As things are
now, I can say 'Fuck You' in a post and not be censored for it.
Amateur radio is controlled by the government; I can't say 'Fuck You'
on the air.  Here, I can say 'marijuana should be legalized' and
'Steve Jackson was innocent'.  If I say those things (or at least the
first one) in a public setting, parents groups get on my case for
corrupting 'our' youth (in one case, someone said I was a messenger of
Satan.  I found that amusing, to say the least.).  People can say
whatever they want, but when they start chasing me with knives and
clubs, you know something is wrong.

If the net comes under govt. control, the government will start
sending its men in black after posters who disagree with it.  Look
what happened to the Black Panthers.  Look what happened to the 2600
meeting just a few months ago.  Read the DOJ Asset Forfeiture Manual -- 
scary stuff.

